.TH "bcm63xx_ep0_internal_request" 9 "bcm63xx_ep0_internal_request" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
bcm63xx_ep0_internal_request \- Helper function to submit an ep0 request.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" bcm63xx_ep0_internal_request
.BI "(struct bcm63xx_udc *udc "  ","
.BI "int ch_idx "  ","
.BI "int length "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "udc" 12
Reference to the device controller.
.IP "ch_idx" 12
IUDMA channel number.
.IP "length" 12
Number of bytes to TX/RX.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Used for simple transfers performed by the ep0 worker.  This will always
use ep0_ctrl_req / ep0_ctrl_buf.
